\begin{align*}
28 &= 27 \cdot 1 + 1 \\
\end{align*}
Subtracting $27$ times the second line from the first line, we get:
\begin{align*}
1 &= 28 - 27 \\
&= 28 \cdot 1 + 27 \cdot (-1) \\
\end{align*}
